  "response_text": "It opens on a bright white surface covered with neatly arranged eyeglasses and sunglasses in rows. The frames vary in shape and colour: clear, grey, black, blue, pale pink, and tinted sunglasses. A light-skinned hand reaches in from the lower right and selects a black rectangular pair from the centre. As the glasses are lifted away, the words “WARBY PARKER” appear printed in grey capital letters beneath them on the white background.\n\nA single pair of tortoiseshell eyeglasses is then presented against a plain white background. The frame has rounded rectangular lenses with warm brown, amber, and dark mottled colouring, and the clear lenses catch soft reflections.\n\nA blonde adult woman with fair skin appears facing forward against the same clean white setting. She wears translucent blue eyeglasses and a teal textured top or sweater. With both hands raised near her temples, she adjusts the glasses, then lowers her hands. Her expression shifts from neutral to a relaxed smile, showing that the frames sit comfortably on her face.\n\nAnother close view shows an adult woman with medium-brown skin and dark curly hair wearing amber-coloured translucent eyeglasses. Her eyes are closed at first, then she opens them and glances toward the viewer. The warm honey tone of the frames stands out against the simple white background.\n\nA light-skinned adult man with short hair and light stubble appears in clear-framed glasses and a pale green shirt. He faces forward with a slight smile, leaning in casually. The clear frames are subtle, with transparent rims and temples.\n\nA pale translucent pair of roundish eyeglasses is shown on its own, the lenses and bridge enlarged against white. Soon after, a young adult man with medium-brown skin and short curly hair wears a similar pale greenish-clear pair. He looks slightly upward toward the viewer with a calm, steady expression, then his face relaxes into a faint smile.\n\nAnother product close-up features clear eyeglasses with a thin reddish-brown tortoiseshell detail around the inner rim. The frame is angled so the lens, bridge, and temple arm are visible, emphasizing the transparent material and patterned accent.\n\nThe scene shifts to a tabletop viewed from above. A dark grey box sits in the centre with white text reading “WARBY PARKER Home Try-On.” Two hands hold the box and lift the lid, revealing several eyeglass frames arranged inside in separate slots. Around the box are tidy lifestyle objects: at upper left, a blue tray or notebook with paper clips; at upper right, a glass cup with amber liquid; and to the right, scattered blue and black puzzle pieces.\n\nA blonde woman in a bright red top sits at a white table beside the opened Home Try-On box. She wears one pair of glasses pushed up on her head and another pair hanging from her neckline. Holding a white hand mirror, she smiles as if checking how a frame looks on her face. A small potted plant sits to her left, and a drink with colourful straws or pencils is on the table near the box.\n\nInside a Warby Parker store, a young adult woman employee stands smiling directly forward. She has long dark hair, wears glasses, and is dressed in a blue work shirt with small white Warby Parker branding and pins on the chest. Behind her, warmly lit shelves display rows of eyeglass frames. The store interior is then shown more widely: bright, orderly, and symmetrical, with wall displays of glasses on both sides, a round wooden display table in the centre, and a colourful geometric mural on the back wall.\n\nEye exam tools and paperwork are laid out neatly on a white surface: a pair of glasses, handheld exam instruments, a black occluder-like tool, a clipboard with a Warby Parker form, a blue pencil, and a printed sheet. The arrangement suggests the in-store eye exam service mentioned in the accompanying context.\n\nA phone app is shown from above on a white desk. A hand holds the smartphone while another finger taps the screen, where different eyeglass frames appear in a shopping-style layout. Around the phone are more glasses, a blue notebook with a gold keychain or clip, and a striped cup of dark coffee, all arranged cleanly and minimally.\n\nThe app demonstration continues with a phone held upright. On the phone screen, a woman with medium-brown skin and short curly hair appears as if using a live selfie view; virtual eyeglass frames are positioned on her face. Blue buttons and small labels appear at the bottom of the screen, though most of the text is too small to read clearly. The woman on the phone touches near her temple and then smiles, showing the virtual try-on effect.\n\nThe same woman is then seen in the room holding a white smartphone in front of her. She wears a light grey turtleneck sweater, sits at a white table with small objects spread out, and smiles broadly at the phone. Her free hand rests under her chin in a playful, pleased pose.\n\nThe young man with the pale clear glasses reappears in close view, resting his cheek on his hand and smiling softly. Then a pair of sunglasses is shown alone: dark blue or charcoal frames with large squared lenses that fade from pale blue to darker grey-green tint.\n\nThe blonde woman appears again, now without glasses, facing forward in a very close view. Her blue eyes are prominent, and she gives a small, knowing smile.\n\nThe commercial ends on simple graphic cards. First, large turquoise text on white reads “We’ve got.” Then a turquoise circle fills the screen with the white “WARBY PARKER” logo. Beneath it, smaller white text reads “PRESCRIPTION GLASSES STARTING AT $95,” and at the bottom appears “WARBYPARKER.COM.”",
